column5: I'm a long time reader of the forum, but now I'm a real member. I'm excited get to know some new guys and share our love for the north woods.
Welcome to the community. Looking forward to your input.
Welcome. How far North are those woods you speak of?
Walcome  Pay no mind to the Wal Mart greeter.LOL  Welcome and yes,how far wood north are ya?
welcome im a northerner myself. north of ohio.
Always room for one more around here, pull up a chair and stay for a spell! Welcome!
Welcome...     So tiller or console, sorry couldn't resist LOL

I should be clear I certainly don’t live up north, but sure wish I did.  I live in Iowa and enjoy camping and fishing the “bush country” as often as I can.  I like to be off the beaten path the adventure is half the fun for me.  Lately, I’ve been going quite a ways north of Pickle Lake beautiful and peaceful area.  My next area of Ontario I would like see is the whole Lake Nipigon region. Oh, by the way, tiller…of course lol. Thanks
